[1-6]	Paul writes another "trustworthy saying".
He lists qualifications for being an overseer in the church.
Above reproach:
Husband of one wife:
Sober-minded: Even tempered.
Lit.:
Neither hot nor cold.
Self-controlled:
Respectable:
Hospitable: Open, welcoming.
Able to teach: Ability to communicate.
Not a drunkard:
Not violent but gentle:
Not quarrelsome:
Not a lover of money:
Ability to manage a household: A sign of which is submissive children.
Not a recent convert:
Of good repute with outsiders:

[8-13]	For deacons, a similar list is made.
Deacons: lit.
table waiter.

